  "doc_id": "18825",
  "text": "Some AeroMACS services can benefit from a flexible asymmetric ratio of the number of OFDMA symbols assigned to downlink (DL) and uplink (UL) channels. This concept is studied in [CITATION_1] . Their research is based on the fact that AeroMACS's TDD framework supports different shares of throughput between DL and UL, which can be beneficial for many UAV applications. They provide a comprehensive analysis of different DL/UL symbol ratio. The examined ratios are based on the cell constraints and data rate requirements. The main focus of the paper is on real-time applications such as video surveillance and sensors.",
